# Our Setup, Import Libaries, Create our Imshow Function and Download our Images
import cv2
import numpy as np
from matplotlib import pyplot as plt

# Define our imshow function 
def imshow(title = "Image", image = None, size = 10):
    w, h = image.shape[0], image.shape[1]
    aspect_ratio = w/h
    plt.figure(figsize=(size * aspect_ratio,size))
    plt.imshow(cv2.cvtColor(image, cv2.COLOR_BGR2RGB))
    plt.title(title)
    plt.show()

Translations - Tasvirni ko'chirish¶

Bu affin transformatsiyasi ya'ni rasmni pozitsiyasini ko'chirish. (left or right).

cv2.warpAffine funksiyasidan foydalanamiz buning uchun.

cv2.warpAffine(image, T, (width, height))

In [18]:
#load image 
image = cv2.imread('Datasets/images/Origin_of_Species.jpg')
imshow("image", image) 

height, width = image.shape[:2] 

#shift qilish uchun kordinatalarni aniqlab olamiz. Misol uchun chorak
chorak_height, chorak_width = int(height/4), int(width/4)

#T matrix pointlarni yaratib olamiz. Yuqoridagi rasmdagi namunadek
#       | 1 0 Tx |
#  T  = | 0 1 Ty | huddi shunday tarzda
T = np.float32([[1, 0, chorak_width], [0, 1, chorak_height]]) #float32 bolishi shart

img_translation = cv2.warpAffine(image, T, (width,height))

imshow('Shifted image', img_translation)

Rotations - Aylanishlar ¶

cv2.getRotationMatrix2D(rotation_center_x, rotation_center_y, angle of rotation, scale) - burilish matrixini hosil qilish. Ya'ni M matrix

In [51]:
# Load our image
image = cv2.imread('Datasets/images/Volleyball.jpeg')
height, width = image.shape[:2] 

# kordinatalarini ikiga bolish orqali sentr point atrofida aylantiramiz
#scale argumenti rasmni mos tushishi agar kattaroq volsa zoom out boladi 
rotation_matrix = cv2.getRotationMatrix2D((width/2, height/2), 90, 1)  #90 counter clockwise direction , 1 - scale 
print(rotation_matrix)

#input rasm rotatition matrix va dsize- desired size kirtiladi                                                
rotated_image = cv2.warpAffine(src=image, M=rotation_matrix, dsize=(width, height))

imshow("Rotated 90 degrees with scale = 1", rotated_image)

[[ 6.123234e-17  1.000000e+00  2.800000e+02]
 [-1.000000e+00  6.123234e-17  1.000000e+03]]
In [50]:
# Divide by two to rototate the image around its centre
rotation_matrix = cv2.getRotationMatrix2D((width/2, height/2), 90, 0.5)

# Input our image, the rotation matrix and our desired final width and height
rotated_image = cv2.warpAffine(image, rotation_matrix, (1500, 1000))
imshow("Rotated 90 degrees with scale = 0.5", rotated_image)
